The error message you're seeing is related to the manifest version being used in your extension. Manifest version 2 is now deprecated, and support will be removed in 2023.

To fix this issue, you need to update the `manifest_version` field in your `manifest.json` file to version 3. Along with this, you'll need to update the other fields and properties in the manifest file to match the format of the version 3 manifest.

Here's an example of how the updated manifest file should look like:


```
{
 "manifest\_version": 3,
 "name": "LinkedIn Lookup Extension",
 "version": "1.0",
 "permissions": [
 "activeTab",
 "https://\*.seek.com.au/\*"
 ],
 "content\_scripts": [
 {
 "matches": ["https://www.seek.com.au/\*"],
 "js": ["content.js"]
 }
 ],
 "browser\_action": {
 "default\_popup": "popup.html"
 }
}
```
It's important to note that this change is not only to fix the error message you're seeing but also to ensure that your extension will continue to work after the support for version 2 is removed.

You can visit the following link to get more information about the changes in manifest version 3 <https://developer.chrome.com/docs/extensions/manifestV3>

And also, it's important to test your extension after making these changes to ensure that it's still working correctly.

