Note that if the parameter name in the `@ModelAttribute` annotation matches the name of a request parameter, Spring will automatically bind the request parameter to the corresponding property of the model object. If the parameter names do not match, you can use the `name` attribute of the `@ModelAttribute` annotation to specify the request parameter name to bind to the model object.

