 userService.addUser(user);
 return ResponseEntity.ok().build();
}
```
In summary, `@ResponseBody` is used to serialize the response from a controller method and send it back to the client, while `@RequestBody` is used to deserialize the incoming request body into an object that can be processed by the server.

